<item>
            <title>[OAK-155] Query: limited support for the deprecated JCR 1.0 query language Query.SQL</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-155</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Existing applications (as well as the TCK) use the JCR 1.0 query language&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;sql&quot;. As far as I know, there are only few differences between JCR 1.0 SQL and JCR 2.0 SQL-2. To make old applications work with Oak, I suggest we provide support JCR 1.0 SQL as well. An additional advantage is that more of the existing TCK tests can be run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I currently don&apos;t know if the full JCR 1.0 SQL syntax can be supported (similar to XPath); if we find supporting certain features is too complicated we will document those limitations instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12596226">OAK-155</key>
